reviews.review_text:
best aud of the bunch watch out for the firecrackers people!

a favorite comes a time comes out of an unlikely place - the feel like a stranger jam

HOT, capital H,O,T. I had some recording of this show from a while back and always figured it was a good show but I never heard it as good as this version.  If you don't put this version of this show in your top whatever, I'll never talk to you again.

Sincerley,
Your Old Friend

Comes A Time A great Stranger-->Comes A Time. I started seeing the Dead in '78 and had a tape of this when I was in high school. I was always jealous of the people that got to see this show, particulary because of the Comes A Time. I didn't see Comes A Time until the '85 breakout at The Greeks (6/14/85). Always one of my favorite Jerry ballads.

Night to remember One of my 1st 10 shows, never saw another like it. Floor seats 14th row center aisle seats. Can't remember what was first, the M-80's or the cretins they had clearing the aisles from dancing. Big Fat dudes that would kick you in the legs! Stayed on the floor below the Band and this girl and I kept trying to go up to their floor and getting kicked out. Overall it was GRATE !

Great dead Was at the show taped it myself,still have the masters somewhere along with about 100 other boots of the Dead, Little Feat, Jefferson Airplane ,the Doors etc. on cassette, lots o early stuff like the warlocks and jerry and Sarah , ever put them to disk. I was way way back so this copy is better than mine, but what a great show up there with RadioCity for me
